# i18n and locales

- All user-facing text in the UI goes through i18n: `useTranslation()` and `t('key')`.
- Interpolation: `t('key', { param: value })` (e.g. `t('mihomo.countProxies', { count: n })`).
- **Keys**: format `feature.section.key` (as in the project: `proxyToolkit.title`, `mihomo.emptyStatus`).

When adding new UI text you **must** add the key and string to both files:
- `src/locales/en.json`
- `src/locales/ru.json`

Example: new heading in mihomo feature → add `"mihomo.newSectionTitle": "..."` to en.json and ru.json, use `t('mihomo.newSectionTitle')` in code.
